# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-48282
# Product:   coldfusion
# Tags:      [KEV] [RCE] [CRIT] [POC]
# Score:     130
# Tier:      CRITICAL — ACT NOW
# Generated: 2026-07-14T11:51:09.653985Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: PoC known — see [6][7]. 4 public proof-of-concept(s) are known to exist.
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline — this
# pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# CVE-2026-48282 — Adobe ColdFusion path traversal leading to RCE (APSB26-68).
# Affected versions: ColdFusion <= 2025.9 and <= 2023.20 [1].
# CISA KEV confirmed; actively exploited in the wild [2].
# Network-exploitable: AV:N/PR:N/UI:N, CVSS 10.0 CRITICAL [1].
#
# Match rationale: ColdFusion path traversal attacks targeting RCE commonly
# abuse the ColdFusion RDS (Remote Development Service) HTTP endpoint
# (/CFIDE/main/ide.cfm, /CFIDE/componentutils/, or similar restricted
# CFIDE paths). The PoC repository names reference "coldfusion-rds-detection"
# [6][7], indicating the RDS interface is the attack surface. Path traversal
# sequences (../, %2e%2e%2f, etc.) embedded in requests to CFIDE paths are
# the observable network indicator targeted by this rule.
#
# The advisory (APSB26-68) and watchTowr Labs research [3] confirm improper
# path restriction in the ColdFusion server component reachable over HTTP.
# Shadowserver honeypot data [4] shows active scanning against this CVE.
#
# ANALYST REVIEW REQUIRED before deployment. This is a proposed draft.
# The PCRE below matches common path traversal encodings; tune threshold
# and HOME_NET port list ($CF_PORTS or 8500,80,443) to your environment.
# False-positive risk: moderate — CFIDE requests without traversal sequences
# are routine in ColdFusion deployments; the traversal content match is
# the primary discriminator.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-48282 Adobe ColdFusion RDS path traversal RCE attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri;
  content:"/CFIDE/"; nocase;
  pcre:"/\/CFIDE\/[^?#]*(?:\.\.(?:\/|%2f)|%2e%2e(?:%2f|\/)|%252e%252e)/iU";
  http.method; content:!"HEAD";
  reference:cve,2026-48282;
  reference:url,labs.watchtowr.com/its-37oc-and-all-we-can-think-about-is-coldfusion-adobe-coldfusion-security-bulletin-apsb26-68-cve-bonanza/;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev true, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-admin;
  sid:9000048; rev:1; )

